HEADWORD: Refluent
<hw>Ref"lu*ent</hw> <pr>(-<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>refluens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>refluere</ets> to flow back; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>fluere</ets> to flow. See
<er>Flurent</er>.]</ety> <def>Flowing back; returning; ebbing.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>refluent</qex> through the pass of fear⟦br⟧
The battle's tide was poured.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

